13.21	Christopher_Knowles	Christopher Knowles	Christopher Knowles (born 1959) is an American poet. In 1976, his poetry was used by Robert Wilson for the avant-garde minimalist Philip Glass opera, Einstein on the Beach In 2004 Knowles stayed in Long Island for the summer working with Robert Wilson. Knowles and Wilson continue to collaborate. Wilson has used Knowles' texts in many of his operas.	
